file=Engineering/ops/custom/incident-response/assets/postmortem-template.md · p—[:Post-Mortem — [incident id] — [date]=> Blameless: name systems, conditions, and decisions — never culprits. Incomplete until the Feeds section is done. Structure adapted with credit from SRE convention (marketplace: sre-incident-response) and bound to this department's annealing loop.\n · s:=- **Severity:** P[0-3] \· **User impact:** [what users experienced, how many, how long]\n- **Duration:** detected [t] → mitigated [t] → resolved [t]\n · tb=\| Time \| What happened / what was done \| Source \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| \| \| \| · cf(:Contributing factors (systems, not saints)=1. [factor — condition/design/process that allowed this; no names-as-causes]\n · wh:worked / what failed=- **Worked:** [detection, rollback, comms — keep doing]\n- **Failed / was missing:** [gaps — each becomes an action item or feed]\n · rc:Rail check=- Data changes during mitigation: [none / operator-run script refs — Rail 3 held ✓]\n- Any off-plan action: [none / halt record ref]\n · f(—:Feeds (MANDATORY — post-mortem is incomplete without these)=- [ ] quinn regression-map entry: [RM-ref] — or written why-not: ___\n- [ ] dev ADR (if design flaw exposed): [ref / n.a. because ___]\n- [ ] maintenance-hygiene: baseline/alert updates: [refs / none needed because ___]\n- [ ] Recurrence check: prior incidents at this fragility? [none / refs → escalate to dev]\n · tb=\| Item \| Owner \| Due \| Done \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| \| \| \| \|